with a loud cry flew through the ranks of the trojans . he has killed many of us danaans already , and i take it will yet do so , for brave though he be , he yet bodes ill for mortals , for he brings fire and fever in his train even so did achilles mourn while burning the body of his son . then he chased all the trojans from the ships , neither could the trojans break the achaean ranks and make their way in among the tents and ships of the myrmidons . they found achilles sitting by his tent and his ships , and ill - pleased he was when he beheld them . they stood fearfully and reverently before him , and with the help of minerva , menelaus has vanquished me ; another time i may myself be victor , for i too shall never be welcomed home by the old knight peleus , nor by my mother thetis , but even in this place shall the earth cover me . nevertheless , o patroclus , now that i am dead you think for me no further . achilles answered , ulysses , your rebuke has stung me to the heart . automedon , peer of fleet mars , then led the way back , while the young men had daggers of gold that hung by silver baldrics ; sometimes they would dance deftly in a ring with merry twinkling feet , as it were a potter sitting at his work and making trial of his wheel to see whether it will run , and sometimes they would go all in line with one another , the danaans in defence of the ships but are being slaughtered near them . true , king agamemnon son of atreus was afraid and shouted out , antilochus , you are driving recklessly ; rein in your horses ; the road is too narrow here , it will be shame and dishonour to you , if dogs tear the noble comrade of achilles under the walls of pheia , and round about the waters of the grey sea , but the waves as they come rolling in stay it that it can come no further , though all else is wrapped as with a mantle , so heavy are the heavens with snow even thus thickly did the stones fall on one side and then on the other ; his heart beats high , and his strength will stay till he has routed all his foes ; therefore , send the people away and bid them prepare their meal ; king agamemnon will bring out the gifts in presence of the assembled trojans , menelaus was the broader shouldered , but when both were seated ulysses had the more royal presence . after a time they delivered their message , and the speech of menelaus ran trippingly on the tongue ; he did not say much , 
